  {
    "ts": "2026-04-22T09:59:27+00:00",
    "headline": "Deutsche Telekom exploring merger with T-Mobile, Bloomberg News reports",
    "summary": "<body><p>STORY: Deutsche Telekom is considering a full combination with T-Mobile US...</p><p>and it could result in the largest public M&A deal on record.</p><p>Bloomberg News reported the story on Tuesday, citing people familiar with the matter.</p><p>The German telecoms group has been in talks about creating a new holding company...</p><p>that would make a stock bid for shares of both Deutsche Telekom and T-Mobile.</p><p>Deutsche Telekom is the majority shareholder in T-Mobile.</p><p>According to LSEG data it has a stake of nearly 53%.</p><p>Shares of T-Mobile, which has a market value of about $218 billion, rose more than 1% following the news.</p><p>Deutsche Telekom has a valuation of about $166 billion.</p><p>In February, the company said it had no plans to sell any T-Mobile shares in 2026.</p><p>The potential merger could create the world's biggest wireless operator by market capitalization.</p><p>The report added that discussions are at a preliminary stage and any transaction would require political support to move ahead.</p><p>Deutsche Telekom and T-Mobile declined to comment when contacted by Reuters.</p><p>The White House and the Federal Network Agency, the primary regulatory body overseeing telecommunications in Germany, did not immediately respond to requests.</p></body>",
    "url": "https://finance.yahoo.com/video/deutsche-telekom-exploring-merger-t-095927014.html",
    "source": "Reuters Videos",
    "provider": "yfinance",
